ly rejected the split, and as of May 2021 the AOS North American Committee has not considered it and the Clements taxonomy has not adopted it. Confusingly, BirdLife International uses the scientific name A. moesta for blue seedeater, but the IOC, AOS, and Clements assign that binomial to blackish-blue seedeater. The BirdLife account encompasses what are now Cabanis's, Ecuadorian, and blackish-blue seedeaters. The Ecuadorian seedeater is monotypic. Description The male Ecuadorian seedeater is mostly a pale slate blue; its crown is a lighter indigo. The female's upperparts are cinnamon and the underparts tawny. Distribution and habitat The Ecuadorian seedeater is found on the west slope of the Andes from southwestern Colombia's Nariño Department through western and central Ecuador into northern Peru, perhaps as far south as the Department of Piura. It inhabits openings in and edges of humid montane and secondary forest and is closely associated with bamboo. In elevation it ranges mostly from 1,100 to 2,300 m (3,600 to 7,500 ft) and locally as low as 800 m (2,600 ft). Behavior Feeding The Ecuadorian seedeater's diet includes insects, seeds, and bamboo shoots. Breeding No information about the Ecuadorian seedeater' breeding phenology has been published. Vocalization An example of the Ecuadorian seedeater's song is [1]. Its call is [2]. Status The IUCN has not assessed the Ecuadorian seedeater. References External links Xeno-canto: audio recordings of the Ecuadorian seedeater", "shortSummary": "The Ecuadorian seedeater (Amaurospiza aequatorialis) is a species of bird in the cardinal family Cardinalidae that the International Ornith…", "locations": ["次生林"], "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5a/Amaurospiza_aequatorialis_-_Ecuadorian_Seedeater_%28cropped%29.jpg/960px-Amaurospiza_aequatorialis_-_Ecuadorian_Seedeater_%28cropped%29.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-amaurospiza", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-amaurospiza-aequatorialis", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-amaurospiza", "species": "taxonomy-species-amaurospiza-aequatorialis"}, "expandable": true, "x": 691.94, "y": -683.48, "z": 606.9}, {"id": "taxonomy-genus-amaurospiza", "name": "Amaurospiza", "latinName": "Amaurospiza", "type": "taxonomy", "taxonomyLevel": "genus", "summary": "Amaurospiza（Amaurospiza）是图谱中的分类级分类节点，当前关联3种鸟类，如Blue seedeater、Ecuadorian seedeater、Carrizal seedeater。", "expandable": true, "memberCount": 3, "x": 523.03, "y": -59.44, "z": -28.71}], "links": [{"key": "bird-ecuadorian-seedeater-f2f631e7__belongs_to_species__taxonomy-species-amaurospiza-aequatorialis", "source": "bird-ecuadorian-seedeater-f2f631e7", "target": "taxonomy-species-amaurospiza-aequatorialis", "relation": "belongs_to_species", "label": "属于种", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 中的种字段补充。"}, {"key": "taxonomy-species-amaurospiza-aequatorialis__belongs_to_genus__taxonomy-genus-amaurospiza", "source": "taxonomy-species-amaurospiza-aequatorialis", "target": "taxonomy-genus-amaurospiza", "relation": "belongs_to_genus", "label": "属于属", "evidence": "依据 birds.csv 分类字段补充：Ecuadorian seedeater 属于属 Amaurospiza。"}]}
